<br>
I skined my chat boxes and hotkeys/group/pet, I made my targetbar transparent so only the name (larger font so easy to read) and the guage show when I have a target (guage is about 5x larger than default).  I made my player window transparent and replaced my sta bar with a xp bar, I'm planing on putting hp/hp:ac:int there sometime, and when I'm 50+ (should be soon, just started over on KB) I'll add an aaxp bar.<br>
<br>
I set my player window transparent 0% so that it's just guages on a black background, and turned spells down to 5% unless mouseover, I think sometime I'll move icons to spellbook if possible and just make a list of spell names on right side of screen (preferable with no background).  I am planing on trying to implment a cleaner guage for the target bar also, I'd really love it if I could pull of a guage that updates just as fast as the old target (have you noticed when switching from one npc to the next it takes up to a second to refresh, but pc to npc it does it instantly)<br>
<br>
It's far from perfect, and probably not even usable for anyone other than myself, but it's getting there.  I'll post a SS if I remember tonight (at work now).<br>
<br>
<br>
HUGE TIP:  if you leave large areas of non-rendered area, don't turn the boxes to transparent.  I thought this looked cool (having a small &quot;wide screen window&quot; with black and text/guages on it) but it gives you a headach shortly due to the huge contrast, if you give it something that averages to 125((r+g+b)/3) or so it's much easier on your head.  Also your &quot;middle&quot; will shift slightly from the middle of your screen if you offset your window like I did, but no scaling is done (it just truncates from the top and bottom, if you keep it in proportion it scales automatically). <br>
<br>
<br>
